title <size:18>Traffic Management System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Signal turns green for Road A. Timer counts down. Sensor detects congestion. System adapts timing. Emergency vehicle approaching — override to green."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class TrafficManagementService <<Facade>> {
    - intersections : Map<String, Intersection>
    - centralController : CentralController
    - emergencyHandler : EmergencyHandler
    - sensorManager : SensorManager
    - analyticsService : AnalyticsService
    --
    + addIntersection(intersection) : void
    + startSystem() : void
    + stopSystem() : void
    + handleEmergency(vehicleId, route) : void
    + getTrafficStatus(intersectionId) : IntersectionStatus
    + overrideSignal(intersectionId, roadId, signal) : void
    + getAnalytics(from, to) : TrafficReport
}

note top of TrafficManagementService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "A city has multiple intersections, each
    with traffic lights. TrafficManagementService
    is the **Facade** — manages all intersections,
    handles emergencies, collects analytics.
    Traffic control center talks only to this."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: ROAD + INTERSECTION MODEL
' ====================================================================
class Intersection {
    - intersectionId : String
    - name : String
    - location : Location
    - roads : List<Road>
    - signalController : SignalController
    - sensors : List<TrafficSensor>
    --
    + getRoads() : List<Road>
    + getSignalController() : SignalController
    + getCurrentStatus() : IntersectionStatus
}

class Road {
    - roadId : String
    - name : String
    - direction : Direction
    - laneCount : int
    - currentSignal : TrafficSignal
    - vehicleQueue : int
    - speedLimit : int
    --
    + getCurrentSignal() : TrafficSignal
    + setSignal(signal) : void
    + getVehicleQueue() : int
    + getCongestionLevel() : CongestionLevel
}

class Location {
    - latitude : double
    - longitude : double
    --
    + distanceTo(other) : double
}

enum Direction {
    NORTH
    SOUTH
    EAST
    WEST
    NORTH_EAST
    NORTH_WEST
    SOUTH_EAST
    SOUTH_WEST
}

enum CongestionLevel {
    FREE_FLOW
    LIGHT
    MODERATE
    HEAVY
    GRIDLOCK
}

note top of Intersection #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Physical layout.**
    "**Intersection** is the core entity — a
    junction where multiple Roads meet.
    Each Road has a direction, lane count,
    current signal state, and a vehicle queue
    (how many cars are waiting).
    CongestionLevel derived from queue length."
end note

Intersection *-- Road : has roads >
Intersection --> Location
Road --> Direction
Road --> CongestionLevel


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: TRAFFIC SIGNAL — State Pattern
' ====================================================================
class TrafficLight {
    - lightId : String
    - road : Road
    - currentState : TrafficSignalState
    - signal : TrafficSignal
    - remainingSeconds : int
    - observers : List<SignalObserver>
    --
    + changeState(state) : void
    + tick() : void
    + getCurrentSignal() : TrafficSignal
    + getRemainingSeconds() : int
    + forceSignal(signal) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

enum TrafficSignal {
    RED
    YELLOW
    GREEN
    BLINKING_RED
    BLINKING_YELLOW
    OFF
}

interface TrafficSignalState <<State>> {
    + onEnter(light) : void
    + onTick(light) : void
    + onExit(light) : void
    + canTransitionTo(signal) : boolean
    + getDuration() : int
}

class GreenState {
    - durationSeconds : int
    --
    + onEnter(light) : void
    + onTick(light) : void
    + getDuration() : int
    + canTransitionTo(signal) : boolean
}

class YellowState {
    - durationSeconds : int
    --
    + onEnter(light) : void
    + onTick(light) : void
    + getDuration() : int
    + canTransitionTo(signal) : boolean
}

class RedState {
    - durationSeconds : int
    --
    + onEnter(light) : void
    + onTick(light) : void
    + getDuration() : int
    + canTransitionTo(signal) : boolean
}

class BlinkingRedState {
    + onEnter(light) : void
    + onTick(light) : void
    + canTransitionTo(signal) : boolean
}

class OffState {
    + onEnter(light) : void
    + onTick(light) : void
    + canTransitionTo(signal) : boolean
}

note bottom of TrafficSignalState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 3 - Signal lifecycle. (KEY STEP)**
    "**State Pattern** — each signal color is
    a class with its own behavior."

    "**GreenState**: counts down durationSeconds.
    When timer hits 0, transitions to Yellow.
    **YellowState**: 3-5 seconds warning,
    transitions to Red.
    **RedState**: waits for controller to
    grant green to this road.
    **BlinkingRed**: malfunction / low traffic.
    **Off**: system shutdown."

    "canTransitionTo() enforces safety:
    Green -> Yellow -> Red -> Green.
    Green -> Red NEVER (must go through Yellow).
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**"
end note

TrafficSignalState <|.. GreenState
TrafficSignalState <|.. YellowState
TrafficSignalState <|.. RedState
TrafficSignalState <|.. BlinkingRedState
TrafficSignalState <|.. OffState
TrafficLight --> TrafficSignalState : delegates >
TrafficLight --> TrafficSignal
TrafficLight --> Road : controls >
Intersection *-- TrafficLight : has lights >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: SIGNAL CONTROLLER — Timing Strategy
' ====================================================================
class SignalController {
    - intersection : Intersection
    - timingStrategy : TimingStrategy
    - lights : Map<String, TrafficLight>
    - currentPhase : int
    - phases : List<SignalPhase>
    --
    + start() : void
    + stop() : void
    + tick() : void
    + advancePhase() : void
    + overridePhase(roadId, signal) : void
    + setTimingStrategy(strategy) : void
}

class SignalPhase {
    - greenRoadIds : Set<String>
    - durationSeconds : int
    --
    + getGreenRoads() : Set<String>
    + getDuration() : int
}

interface TimingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + calculatePhaseDurations(intersection) : List<SignalPhase>
}

class FixedTimingStrategy {
    - greenDuration : int
    - yellowDuration : int
    - redDuration : int
    --
    + calculatePhaseDurations(intersection) : List<SignalPhase>
}

class AdaptiveTimingStrategy {
    - sensorManager : SensorManager
    - minGreen : int
    - maxGreen : int
    --
    + calculatePhaseDurations(intersection) : List<SignalPhase>
}

class PeakHourTimingStrategy {
    - peakHourPhases : List<SignalPhase>
    - offPeakPhases : List<SignalPhase>
    --
    + calculatePhaseDurations(intersection) : List<SignalPhase>
    + isPeakHour() : boolean
}

class RoundRobinTimingStrategy {
    - equalDuration : int
    --
    + calculatePhaseDurations(intersection) : List<SignalPhase>
}

note bottom of TimingStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - How long is each signal?**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — timing is pluggable."

    "**FixedTiming**: green=30s, yellow=5s, red=30s.
    Simple, predictable. Small intersections.
    **AdaptiveTiming**: reads sensor data, gives
    more green time to congested roads.
    **PeakHourTiming**: switches between peak
    and off-peak timing profiles.
    **RoundRobin**: equal time for all roads."

    "Switch strategies at runtime:
    8am-10am: PeakHour. Night: Fixed."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

TimingStrategy <|.. FixedTimingStrategy
TimingStrategy <|.. AdaptiveTimingStrategy
TimingStrategy <|.. PeakHourTimingStrategy
TimingStrategy <|.. RoundRobinTimingStrategy
SignalController --> TimingStrategy : delegates >
SignalController --> SignalPhase : cycles through >
SignalController --> TrafficLight : controls >
Intersection --> SignalController : managed by >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: SENSORS — Observer Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface TrafficSensor <<Observer>> {
    + detect() : SensorReading
    + getType() : SensorType
}

class InductionLoopSensor {
    - location : Location
    --
    + detect() : SensorReading
    + getType() : SensorType
}

class CameraSensor {
    - location : Location
    - resolution : String
    --
    + detect() : SensorReading
    + getType() : SensorType
}

class RadarSensor {
    - location : Location
    --
    + detect() : SensorReading
    + getType() : SensorType
}

class SensorReading {
    - sensorId : String
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - vehicleCount : int
    - averageSpeed : double
    - queueLength : int
    - occupancy : double
}

enum SensorType {
    INDUCTION_LOOP
    CAMERA
    RADAR
    INFRARED
}

class SensorManager {
    - sensors : Map<String, TrafficSensor>
    - observers : List<SensorDataObserver>
    --
    + pollAllSensors() : List<SensorReading>
    + getSensorReading(sensorId) : SensorReading
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    - notifyObservers(reading) : void
}

interface SensorDataObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onSensorData(reading) : void
}

class CongestionDetector {
    - threshold : int
    --
    + onSensorData(reading) : void
}

class AdaptiveTimingUpdater {
    --
    + onSensorData(reading) : void
}

class AnalyticsCollector {
    --
    + onSensorData(reading) : void
}

note bottom of TrafficSensor #B2EBF2
    **STEP 5 - Eyes on the road.**
    "Sensors detect vehicles at each road.
    **Strategy** — sensor type is pluggable:
    InductionLoop (in-ground), Camera (vision),
    Radar (speed). All return SensorReading."

    "SensorManager polls sensors and notifies
    observers. **Observer Pattern**:"
    "**CongestionDetector**: flags heavy traffic.
    **AdaptiveTimingUpdater**: feeds real-time
    data to AdaptiveTimingStrategy.
    **AnalyticsCollector**: logs for reporting."
    **Patterns: Strategy + Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

TrafficSensor <|.. InductionLoopSensor
TrafficSensor <|.. CameraSensor
TrafficSensor <|.. RadarSensor
TrafficSensor --> SensorReading : produces >
TrafficSensor --> SensorType
SensorDataObserver <|.. CongestionDetector
SensorDataObserver <|.. AdaptiveTimingUpdater
SensorDataObserver <|.. AnalyticsCollector
SensorManager --> TrafficSensor : polls >
SensorManager --> SensorDataObserver : notifies >
Intersection --> TrafficSensor : has sensors >
TrafficManagementService --> SensorManager
AdaptiveTimingStrategy --> SensorManager : reads >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: EMERGENCY HANDLING — Command Pattern
' ====================================================================
class EmergencyHandler {
    - commandHistory : List<EmergencyCommand>
    --
    + handleEmergencyVehicle(vehicle, route) : void
    + clearEmergency(vehicleId) : void
}

interface EmergencyCommand <<Command>> {
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

class GreenCorridorCommand {
    - intersections : List<Intersection>
    - route : List<Road>
    - previousStates : Map<String, TrafficSignal>
    --
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

class AllRedCommand {
    - intersection : Intersection
    - previousStates : Map<String, TrafficSignal>
    --
    + execute() : void
    + undo() : void
}

class EmergencyVehicle {
    - vehicleId : String
    - type : EmergencyType
    - currentLocation : Location
    - route : List<Intersection>
    - priority : int
}

enum EmergencyType {
    AMBULANCE
    FIRE_TRUCK
    POLICE
    VIP_CONVOY
}

note bottom of EmergencyCommand #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Ambulance approaching!**
    "**Command Pattern** — emergency overrides
    are reversible commands."

    "**GreenCorridorCommand**: turn all signals
    green along the ambulance route. Saves
    previous states. When ambulance passes,
    undo() restores original signals.
    **AllRedCommand**: stop all traffic at
    an intersection (accident/safety)."

    "Commands are logged for audit.
    Multiple emergencies? Queue them."
    **Pattern: Command | SRP, OCP**
end note

EmergencyCommand <|.. GreenCorridorCommand
EmergencyCommand <|.. AllRedCommand
EmergencyHandler --> EmergencyCommand : executes >
EmergencyHandler --> EmergencyVehicle : tracks >
EmergencyVehicle --> EmergencyType
EmergencyVehicle --> Location
TrafficManagementService --> EmergencyHandler


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: CENTRAL CONTROLLER — Coordination
' ====================================================================
class CentralController {
    - intersectionControllers : Map<String, SignalController>
    - coordinationStrategy : CoordinationStrategy
    --
    + startAll() : void
    + stopAll() : void
    + tickAll() : void
    + coordinateGreenWave(corridor) : void
}

interface CoordinationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + coordinate(controllers) : void
}

class IndependentStrategy {
    + coordinate(controllers) : void
}

class GreenWaveStrategy {
    - corridorSpeed : int
    - offset : int
    --
    + coordinate(controllers) : void
}

class AdaptiveNetworkStrategy {
    + coordinate(controllers) : void
}

note bottom of CoordinationStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Coordinate across intersections.**
    "Individual intersections work alone.
    But a corridor (e.g., a main road with
    5 intersections) needs coordination."

    "**Strategy Pattern:**
    **Independent**: each intersection on its own.
    **GreenWave**: stagger green signals along
    a corridor so a car hitting green at
    intersection 1 hits green at 2, 3, 4, 5.
    **AdaptiveNetwork**: city-wide optimization."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

CoordinationStrategy <|.. IndependentStrategy
CoordinationStrategy <|.. GreenWaveStrategy
CoordinationStrategy <|.. AdaptiveNetworkStrategy
CentralController --> CoordinationStrategy : delegates >
CentralController --> SignalController : manages >
TrafficManagementService --> CentralController


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: SIGNAL OBSERVER — Notifications
' ====================================================================
interface SignalObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onSignalChange(light, oldSignal, newSignal) : void
}

class PedestrianDisplayObserver {
    + onSignalChange(light, oldSignal, newSignal) : void
}

class EmergencyPreemptObserver {
    + onSignalChange(light, oldSignal, newSignal) : void
}

class LoggingObserver {
    + onSignalChange(light, oldSignal, newSignal) : void
}

class VehicleToInfraObserver {
    + onSignalChange(light, oldSignal, newSignal) : void
}

note bottom of SignalObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - React to signal changes.**
    "**Observer Pattern** — on every signal
    change, observers react:"

    "**PedestrianDisplay**: update walk/don't-walk.
    **EmergencyPreempt**: check if emergency
    vehicle is nearby, trigger override.
    **LoggingObserver**: log for audit/analytics.
    **V2I Observer**: broadcast to connected
    vehicles (future smart traffic)."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

SignalObserver <|.. PedestrianDisplayObserver
SignalObserver <|.. EmergencyPreemptObserver
SignalObserver <|.. LoggingObserver
SignalObserver <|.. VehicleToInfraObserver
TrafficLight --> SignalObserver : notifies >


' ====================================================================
'  ANALYTICS
' ====================================================================
class AnalyticsService {
    --
    + getAverageWaitTime(intersectionId) : double
    + getCongestionReport(from, to) : TrafficReport
    + getPeakHours(intersectionId) : List<TimeRange>
}

class TrafficReport {
    - period : String
    - avgWaitTime : double
    - peakCongestion : CongestionLevel
    - totalVehicles : long
    - emergencyCount : int
}

AnalyticsService --> TrafficReport
TrafficManagementService --> AnalyticsService


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Intersections have Roads with TrafficLights.
    Lights cycle Green -> Yellow -> Red via **State Pattern**
    (safety: Green->Red impossible, must go through Yellow).
    SignalController uses **Timing Strategy** (Fixed/Adaptive/PeakHour).
    Sensors detect traffic, feed **Observer** chain (congestion detection,
    adaptive timing, analytics). Emergency vehicles get green corridors
    via reversible **Commands**. Multiple intersections coordinated via
    **Green Wave Strategy**. 6 patterns: **State**, **Strategy** (x3),
    **Observer** (x2), **Command**, **Facade**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Traffic control center calls TrafficManagementService | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Intersection has Roads (direction, lanes, queue, congestion) | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Green -> Yellow -> Red (safety enforced, no skipping Yellow) | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 4 | Fixed / Adaptive / PeakHour / RoundRobin timing | Strategy (timing) | OCP, DIP |
    | 5 | Loop / Camera / Radar sensors detect traffic, feed observers | Strategy + Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 6 | Ambulance: green corridor command, undo when passed | Command | SRP, OCP |
    | 7 | Green wave: stagger signals along corridor for smooth flow | Strategy (coordination) | OCP, DIP |
    | 8 | Pedestrian display, emergency preempt, V2I, logging | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Single Intersection** = Steps 2-4 | **Sensors** = Step 5 | **Emergency** = Step 6 | **City-wide** = Step 7 |
endlegend

@enduml
